HEADWORD: Aposiopesis
<hw>Ap`o*si`o*pe"sis</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <?/, from <?/ to be quite silent.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A figure of speech in which the speaker breaks off suddenly, as if
unwilling or unable to state what was in his mind; <as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧I
declare to you that his conduct -- but I can not speak of <ex>that</ex>,
here</as>.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apositic</ent>⟦br⟧
